      "text": "Issues\n\n- Issues\n- Market Rules\n- Home\n\n## NPRR1270\n\n- Key Documents\n- Background\n- Voting Record\n- Action\n- Summary\n\n#### Summary\n\n12/05/2025\n\n| Title | Additional Revisions Required for Implementation of RTC |\n| --- | --- |\n| Next Group |\n| Next Step |\n| Status | Approved on 05/15/2025 |\n| Effective Dates |\n\n#### Action\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Action Taken | Next Steps |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 05/15/2025 | PUCT | Approved |\n| 04/08/2025 | BOARD | Recommended for Approval | PUCT for consideration |\n| 03/26/2025 | TAC | Recommended for Approval | Board for consideration |\n| 03/12/2025 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | TAC for consideration |\n| 02/12/2025 | PRS | Deferred/Tabled | PRS for consideration |\n\n#### Voting Record\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Motion | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 05/15/2025 | PUCT | To approve NPRR1270 and accompanying ERCOT Market Impact Statement as presented in Project No. 54445, Review of Protocols Adopted by the Independent Organization | Passed |\n| 04/08/2025 | BOARD | To recommend approval of NPRR1270 as recommended by TAC in the 3/26/25 TAC Report | Passed |\n| 03/26/2025 | TAC | To recommend approval of NPRR1270 as recommended by PRS in the 3/12/25 PRS Report | Passed |\n| 03/12/2025 | PRS | To grant NPRR1270 Urgent status; to recommend approval of NPRR1270 as submitted; and to forward to TAC NPRR1270 and the 1/28/25 Impact Analysis | Passed |\n| 02/12/2025 | PRS | To table NPRR1270 | Passed |\n\n#### Background\n\n| Status: | Approved |\n| --- | --- |\n| Date Posted: | Jan 28, 2025 |\n| Sponsor: | ERCOT |\n| Urgent: | Yes |\n| Sections: | 6.5.5.2, 6.5.7.6.2.3, 6.5.9.4.2, 8.1.1.2.1.3, 8.1.1.2.1.7, and 8.1.1.4.3 |\n| Description: | This Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR): Updates requirements for Load Resources that are changing under Real-Time Co-optimization (RTC) and were not updated in earlier revisions; removes language associated with Group assignments in the Day-Ahead Market (DAM); deployments are Resource-specific based on Real-Time awards; no requirement to return to service in three hours as that capacity will be replaced with awarded capacity in Real-Time; eliminates the automatic qualification of all Resources to provide On-Line Non-Spinning Reserve (Non-Spin) and Security-Constrained Economic Dispatch (SCED)-dispatchable ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS). Resources will be required to undergo a qualification test to provide each of these services; and adds additional pre-processing checks in the SCED process to validate Ancillary Service capability telemetry that are sent by Qualified Scheduling Entities (QSEs). |\n| Reason: | General system and/or process improvement(s) |\n\n#### Key Documents\n\n1270NPRR-01 Additional Revisions Required for Implementation of RTC 012825\n\nJan 28, 2025 - docx - 84.7 KB\n\n1270NPRR-02 Impact Analysis 012825\n\nJan 28, 2025 - docx - 30.5 KB\n\n1270NPRR-03 PRS Ballot 021225\n\nFeb 16, 2025 - xls - 141 KB\n\n1270NPRR-04 PRS Report 021225\n\nFeb 16, 2025 - docx - 84.7 KB\n\n1270NPRR-05 PRS Ballot 031225\n\nMar 14, 2025 - xls - 140.5 KB\n\n1270NPRR-06 PRS Report 031225\n\nMar 14, 2025 - docx - 84.7 KB\n\n1270NPRR-07 TAC Ballot 032625\n\nMar 27, 2025 - xls - 160 KB\n\n1270NPRR-08 TAC Report 032625\n\nMar 27, 2025 - docx - 93.5 KB\n\n1270NPRR-09 Board Report 040825\n\nApr 8, 2025 - docx - 93.7 KB\n\n1270NPRR-10 PUCT Report 051525\n\nMay 19, 2025 - docx - 93.5 KB\n\n##### Related Content\n\n###### On this site",
